<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="110" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1452,846,1264]" pageId="3" pageNumber="110">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Saravanan &amp; Kaliamoorthy" authorityYear="2022" box="[136,422,846,867]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Balsaminaceae" genus="Impatiens" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="3" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="kurichiarmalayana">
<emphasis box="[136,422,846,867]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="110">Impatiens kurichiarmalayana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="K. M. P. Kumar, R. Jagad. &amp; Nagaraj (2017: 281)" authorityName="K. M. P. Kumar, R. Jagad. &amp; Nagaraj" authorityPageNumber="281" authorityYear="2017" box="[550,1210,846,868]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Balsaminaceae" genus="Impatiens" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="3" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mankulamensis">
<emphasis box="[550,719,846,867]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="110">I. mankulamensis</emphasis>
K. M. P. Kumar, R. Jagad. &amp; Nagaraj (2017: 281)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="K. M. P. Kumar, R. Jagad. &amp; G. Prasad (2017: 285)" authorityName="K. M. P. Kumar, R. Jagad. &amp; G. Prasad. The" authorityPageNumber="285" authorityYear="2017" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Balsaminaceae" genus="Impatiens" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="3" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="panduranganii">
<emphasis box="[1258,1422,846,867]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="110">I. panduranganii</emphasis>
K. M. P. Kumar, R. Jagad. &amp; G. Prasad (2017: 285)
</taxonomicName>
in having common characters viz., rosulate leaves, umbellate cyme inflorescence, unequally bilobed wing petals and shorter basal lobes. But differs from 
<taxonomicName box="[904,1074,918,939]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Balsaminaceae" genus="Impatiens" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="3" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mankulamensis">
<emphasis box="[904,1074,918,939]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="110">I. mankulamensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having ovate-lanceolate leaves (
<emphasis box="[1431,1451,918,939]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="110">vs</emphasis>
elliptic, lanceolate-oblanceolate in 
<taxonomicName box="[526,695,954,975]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Balsaminaceae" genus="Impatiens" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="3" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mankulamensis">
<emphasis box="[526,695,954,975]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="110">I. mankulamensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), lateral sepals white with dark purple tinges at the apex (
<emphasis box="[1255,1275,954,975]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="110">vs</emphasis>
white with brown tinges at tip in 
<taxonomicName box="[339,508,990,1011]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Balsaminaceae" genus="Impatiens" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="3" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mankulamensis">
<emphasis box="[339,508,990,1011]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="110">I. mankulamensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), dorsal petal white (
<emphasis box="[719,739,990,1011]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="110">vs</emphasis>
pale purple in 
<taxonomicName box="[890,1060,990,1011]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Balsaminaceae" genus="Impatiens" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="3" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mankulamensis">
<emphasis box="[890,1060,990,1011]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="110">I. mankulamensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), presence of dorsal auricle (
<emphasis box="[1348,1368,990,1011]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="110">vs</emphasis>
absence in 
<taxonomicName box="[218,390,1026,1047]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Balsaminaceae" genus="Impatiens" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="3" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mankulamensis">
<emphasis box="[218,390,1026,1047]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="110">I. mankulamensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and absence of spur (
<emphasis box="[627,647,1026,1047]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="110">vs</emphasis>
present in 
<taxonomicName box="[765,937,1026,1047]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Balsaminaceae" genus="Impatiens" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="3" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mankulamensis">
<emphasis box="[765,937,1026,1047]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="110">I. mankulamensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Saravanan &amp; Kaliamoorthy" authorityYear="2022" box="[962,1250,1026,1047]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Balsaminaceae" genus="Impatiens" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="3" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="kurichiarmalayana">
<emphasis box="[962,1250,1026,1047]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="110">Impatiens kurichiarmalayana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="K. M. P. Kumar, R. Jagad. &amp; G. Prasad. The" authorityYear="2017" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Balsaminaceae" genus="Impatiens" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="3" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="panduranganii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="110">I. panduranganii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having white flowers with dark purple spot at the base of the wing petals (
<emphasis box="[1105,1125,1062,1083]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="110">vs</emphasis>
white with light purple dots in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="K. M. P. Kumar, R. Jagad. &amp; G. Prasad. The" authorityYear="2017" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Balsaminaceae" genus="Impatiens" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="3" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="panduranganii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="110">I. panduranganii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), dorsal petal keeled at apex (
<emphasis box="[627,647,1098,1119]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="110">vs</emphasis>
not keeled in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="K. M. P. Kumar, R. Jagad. &amp; G. Prasad. The" authorityYear="2017" box="[788,952,1098,1119]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Balsaminaceae" genus="Impatiens" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="3" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="panduranganii">
<emphasis box="[788,952,1098,1119]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="110">I. panduranganii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), distal lobe spreading and broadly obovate (
<emphasis box="[1394,1414,1098,1119]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="110">vs</emphasis>
not spreading and shoe shaped in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="K. M. P. Kumar, R. Jagad. &amp; G. Prasad. The" authorityYear="2017" box="[477,640,1134,1155]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Balsaminaceae" genus="Impatiens" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="3" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="panduranganii">
<emphasis box="[477,640,1134,1155]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="110">I. panduranganii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), lower sepal white with yellow mark at middle and dark brown streaks horizontally (
<emphasis box="[197,217,1170,1191]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="110">vs</emphasis>
white with yellow tinges in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="K. M. P. Kumar, R. Jagad. &amp; G. Prasad. The" authorityYear="2017" box="[491,654,1170,1191]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Balsaminaceae" genus="Impatiens" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="3" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="panduranganii">
<emphasis box="[491,654,1170,1191]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="110">I. panduranganii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) (
<tableCitation box="[674,748,1170,1192]" captionStart="TABLE 2" captionStartId="4.[136,224,160,184]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="TABLE 2. Distinguishing characters of Impatiens kurichiarmalayana, I. mankulamensis and I. panduranganii." pageId="3" pageNumber="110">Table 2</tableCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
